        "text": "hey <@U0524MK6H3K>, <@U01DZUA88S1> suggested that I look into #18898 and if I understand correctly, the check needed is to confirm that the class \"Pair\" is no longer dropped. I think that is correct now in R 4.6.0:\n\n```&gt; df &lt;- data.frame(response = I(Pair(1,2)))\n&gt; class(df$response)\n[1] \"AsIs\" \"Pair\"\n&gt; class(df[TRUE,,drop=FALSE]$response)\n[1] \"AsIs\" \"Pair\"\n&gt; sessionInfo()\nR version 4.6.0 (2026-04-24)\nPlatform: x86_64-pc-linux-gnu\nRunning under: Arch Linux```",
